summarize the # and % of patients and episodes that lasted 0-3 months, 3-6 months, 6-12 months, and > 12 months

# Assuming the dataset `episode_demo_duration` contains the variables `episode.duration` and `pat_id`

# Create duration categories
episode_demo_duration$duration_category <- cut(
  episode_demo_duration$episode.duration,
  breaks = c(0, 90, 180, 365, Inf), 
  labels = c("0-3 months", "3-6 months", "6-12 months", ">12 months"),
  right = FALSE
)

# Count episodes in each category
episodes_summary <- as.data.frame(table(episode_demo_duration$duration_category))
colnames(episodes_summary) <- c("Duration Category", "Episodes Count")

# Count unique patients in each category
patients_summary <- aggregate(
  pat_id ~ duration_category, 
  data = unique(episode_demo_duration[, c("pat_id", "duration_category")]), 
  FUN = length
)
colnames(patients_summary) <- c("Duration Category", "Patients Count")

# Merge the summaries
summary <- merge(episodes_summary, patients_summary, by = "Duration Category")

# Calculate percentages
summary$`Episodes (%)` <- round((summary$`Episodes Count` / sum(summary$`Episodes Count`)) * 100, 1)
summary$`Patients (%)` <- round((summary$`Patients Count` / length(unique(episode_demo_duration$pat_id))) * 100, 1)

# Print the summary
print(summary)

# Define the summary function for each variable, with Group converted to character and Category added
supptab2 <- function(data, var_name) {
  var <- sym(var_name)  # Convert string to symbol for use with dplyr functions
  
  data %>%
    group_by(!!var, discontinued) %>%
    count() %>%
    group_by(!!var) %>%
    mutate(percentage = n / sum(n) * 100) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    pivot_wider(
      names_from = discontinued,
      values_from = c(n, percentage),
      names_glue = "{discontinued}_{.value}"
    ) %>%
    mutate(
      Discontinued = paste0(`Discontinued_n`, " (", round(`Discontinued_percentage`, 1), "%)"),
      Continued = paste0(`Continued_n`, " (", round(`Continued_percentage`, 1), "%)")
    ) %>%
    select(!!var, Discontinued, Continued) %>%
    rename(Group = !!var) %>%
    mutate(Group = as.character(Group),  # Convert Group to character
           Category = var_name)  # Set Category to the variable name
}

# Function to create a combined summary for each category and compile into a single table
create_combined_summary <- function(data) {
  # Get all column names except "discontinued"
  vars <- setdiff(names(data), "discontinued")
  
  # Apply supptab2 function to each variable and combine results
  combined_summary <- bind_rows(
    lapply(vars, function(var) supptab2(data, var))
  )
  
  # Display the combined summary using gt
  combined_summary %>%
    gt(groupname_col = "Category") %>%
    tab_header(title = "Summary of Episodes by Variable, Discontinued Status, and Count") %>%
    cols_label(
      Group = "Group",
      Continued = "Continued (Count, %)",
      Discontinued = "Discontinued (Count, %)"
    ) %>%
    tab_options(
      table.font.size = "small",
      data_row.padding = px(3)
    )
}

# Run the function on episode_model3_yradd
summary_table <- create_combined_summary(episode_model3_yradd)

SMOTE (Oversampling)

evaluate_models2 <- function(dataset_h2o, predictors, outcome = "discontinued") {
    # Convert the outcome to factor (for classification tasks)
    dataset_h2o[, outcome] <- as.factor(dataset_h2o[, outcome])
    
    # Set common parameters for SMOTE-like class balancing
    balance_params <- list(balance_classes = TRUE, class_sampling_factors = c(1.0, 3.57))  # 3.57 approximates the imbalance
    
    # Logistic Regression
    logit_model <- h2o.glm(
      x = predictors,
      y = outcome,
      training_frame = dataset_h2o,
      family = "binomial",
      nfolds = 10,
      seed = 1234,
      balance_classes = balance_params$balance_classes,
      class_sampling_factors = balance_params$class_sampling_factors  # Apply class balancing parameters
    )
    
    # Random Forest
    rf_model <- h2o.randomForest(
      x = predictors,
      y = outcome,
      training_frame = dataset_h2o,
      nfolds = 10,
      seed = 1234,
      balance_classes = balance_params$balance_classes,
      class_sampling_factors = balance_params$class_sampling_factors
    )
    
    # GBM
    gbm_model <- h2o.gbm(
      x = predictors,
      y = outcome,
      training_frame = dataset_h2o,
      nfolds = 10,
      seed = 1234,
      balance_classes = balance_params$balance_classes,
      class_sampling_factors = balance_params$class_sampling_factors
    )
    
    # Neural Network (MLP with two hidden layers)
    nn_model <- h2o.deeplearning(
      x = predictors,
      y = outcome,
      training_frame = dataset_h2o,
      hidden = c(64, 64),
      activation = "RectifierWithDropout",
      nfolds = 10,
      seed = 1234,
      balance_classes = balance_params$balance_classes,
      class_sampling_factors = balance_params$class_sampling_factors
    )
   
    
    # Get Performance for each model at threshold = 0.5
    get_metrics <- function(model, dataset) {
      perf <- h2o.performance(model, dataset)
      auc <- h2o.auc(perf)
      aucpr <- h2o.aucpr(perf)
      
      # Get metrics at threshold = 0.5
      threshold_0.5 <- 0.5
      accuracy <- h2o.accuracy(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
      precision <- h2o.precision(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
      recall <- h2o.recall(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
      f1 <- h2o.F1(perf, thresholds = threshold_0.5)
      
      list(auc = auc, aucpr = aucpr, precision = precision, recall = recall, accuracy = accuracy, f1 = f1)
    }
    
    # Store metrics for each model
    metrics <- list(
      logistic = get_metrics(logit_model, dataset_h2o),
      random_forest = get_metrics(rf_model, dataset_h2o),
      gbm = get_metrics(gbm_model, dataset_h2o),
      neural_network = get_metrics(nn_model, dataset_h2o)
    )
    
    # Extract ROC and PR curves data for each model
    fpr_logit <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o)))
    tpr_logit <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o)))
    fpr_rf <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o)))
    tpr_rf <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o)))
    fpr_gbm <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o)))
    tpr_gbm <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o)))
    fpr_nn <- as.data.frame(h2o.fpr(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o)))
    tpr_nn <- as.data.frame(h2o.tpr(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o)))
    
    # Combine ROC data for ggplot
    roc_data <- rbind(
      data.frame(FPR = fpr_logit$fpr, TPR = tpr_logit$tpr, Model = "Logistic Regression"),
      data.frame(FPR = fpr_rf$fpr, TPR = tpr_rf$tpr, Model = "Random Forest"),
      data.frame(FPR = fpr_gbm$fpr, TPR = tpr_gbm$tpr, Model = "GBM"),
      data.frame(FPR = fpr_nn$fpr, TPR = tpr_nn$tpr, Model = "Neural Network")
    )
    
    # Plot ROC curves
    roc_plot <- ggplot(roc_data, aes(x = FPR, y = TPR, color = Model)) +
      geom_line(size = 1.2) +
      labs(title = "ROC Curve", x = "False Positive Rate (FPR)", y = "True Positive Rate (TPR)") +
      theme_minimal() +
      scale_color_manual(values = c("blue", "red", "green", "orange")) +
      theme(legend.position = c(0.8, 0.2))  # Legend inside
    
    # Combine PR data for ggplot
    precision_logit <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o))
    recall_logit <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(logit_model, dataset_h2o))
    precision_rf <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o))
    recall_rf <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(rf_model, dataset_h2o))
    precision_gbm <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o))
    recall_gbm <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(gbm_model, dataset_h2o))
    precision_nn <- h2o.precision(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o))
    recall_nn <- h2o.recall(h2o.performance(nn_model, dataset_h2o))
    
    pr_data <- rbind(
      data.frame(Recall = recall_logit$tpr, Precision = precision_logit$precision, Model = "Logistic Regression"),
      data.frame(Recall = recall_rf$tpr, Precision = precision_rf$precision, Model = "Random Forest"),
      data.frame(Recall = recall_gbm$tpr, Precision = precision_gbm$precision, Model = "GBM"),
      data.frame(Recall = recall_nn$tpr, Precision = precision_nn$precision, Model = "Neural Network")
    )
    
    # Plot PR curves
    pr_plot <- ggplot(pr_data, aes(x = Recall, y = Precision, color = Model)) +
      geom_line(size = 1.2) +
      labs(title = "Precision-Recall Curve", x = "Recall", y = "Precision") +
      theme_minimal() +
      scale_color_manual(values = c("blue", "red", "green", "orange")) +
      theme(legend.position = c(0.8, 0.2))  # Legend inside
    
    # Return the metrics and the plots
    return(list(metrics = metrics, roc_plot = roc_plot, pr_plot = pr_plot))
}

  )
